## File Conventions

### Directory Structure

{{#if (eq framework "nextjs")}}
```
app/                    # App Router directory
├── (routes)/          # Route groups
│   └── page.tsx       # Page components
├── api/               # API routes
│   └── */route.ts     # Route handlers
├── layout.tsx         # Root layout
└── globals.css        # Global styles

components/            # Reusable components
lib/                   # Utilities and libraries
public/                # Static assets
```
{{/if}}

{{#if (eq framework "expo")}}
```
app/                   # Expo Router directory
├── (tabs)/           # Tab navigation group
├── _layout.tsx       # Root layout
└── index.tsx         # Home screen

components/           # Reusable components
assets/              # Images, fonts, etc.
hooks/               # Custom hooks
```
{{/if}}

{{#if (eq framework "tanstack-start")}}
```
app/
├── routes/          # File-based routes
│   ├── index.tsx    # Home route
│   └── __root.tsx   # Root route
├── components/      # Components
└── utils/          # Utilities
```
{{/if}}

{{#if (eq framework "astro")}}
```
src/
├── pages/          # File-based routes
├── layouts/        # Layout components
├── components/     # Reusable components
└── content/        # Content collections

public/             # Static assets
```
{{/if}}

{{#if (eq framework "hono")}}
```
src/
├── routes/         # Route handlers
├── middleware/     # Custom middleware
├── utils/          # Utilities
└── index.ts        # App entry point
```
{{/if}}

{{#if (eq framework "elysia")}}
```
src/
├── routes/         # Route handlers
├── plugins/        # Custom plugins
├── utils/          # Utilities
└── index.ts        # App entry point
```
{{/if}}

### Naming Conventions

{{#if hasTypeScript}}
- **TypeScript Files**: Use `.ts` for modules, `.tsx` for components with JSX
- **Type Definitions**: Co-locate types with implementation or use `types.ts` files
- **Interfaces**: Use PascalCase for interface names
{{/if}}

- **Components**: Use PascalCase for component files (e.g., `UserProfile.tsx`)
- **Utilities**: Use camelCase for utility files (e.g., `formatDate.ts`)
- **Constants**: Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants

